Precipitation Detection¶

I think my plate assay has a precipitation problem. Below I plotted all of the traces from my datasets, there are some traces where it looks like someting has precipitated out, because they appear to absorb loads at low wavelengths, which happens when light is scattered due to precipitation.

The aim of this notebook is to find a way to capture the anomalies.

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from PlateAnalysis_Echo import PlateDataset

dataset_1 = PlateDataset('20191105_Dopt_2_Shaking.CSV','D_Opt.csv')
dataset_2 = PlateDataset('20191105_Dopt_2_Shaking_rep2.CSV','D_Opt.csv')
dataset_3 = PlateDataset('20191105_Dopt_2_Shaking_rep3.CSV','D_Opt.csv')

dataset_0.PlotTrace(dataset_0.data,'all')
dataset_1.PlotTrace(dataset_1.data,'all')
dataset_2.PlotTrace(dataset_2.data,'all')
dataset_3.PlotTrace(dataset_3.data,'all')
